The paper focuses on the use of word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of different text representation mechanisms, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also uses modern word embeddings, which are based on neural network models, indicating a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
